The food is always good but the service has declined recently in the takeout context. It's not the servers' fault, it's management changes. They no longer accept pickup orders over the phone. For pickup you must place the order on the website. An automatic 18% gratuity is added. "Automatic gratuities" are self-contradictory in any context, and while I can understand why many restaurants add them to the bill for large parties dining in, I am miffed that they would include one for simply handing me the food across the counter, after requiring me to order from an online form. Tips are for service, and there is zero service happening here. If you do intend to tip in the online order form, realize that any tip you add will be added on top of the automatic tip. You may think you're tipping 18% but you're actually tipping 36%.

I did enjoy the horchata and the chips and salsa. I might have to order something else. The atmosphere is nice, especially the outdoors. The service was okay. I'm at odds here. I do think the food is great (not amazing, but better than any Mexican food you can get in Champaign-Urbana), but man...the service has been a little hellish the two times I've gone. I thought it might have been a fluke the first time, but on a recent trip here, my friends and I were stuck there for over two hours.  When we walked in, around 4 p.m., very few people were at the restaurant, and the hostess seemed annoyed that we wanted to sit outside. We assumed this meant it was super busy outside--nope. There were maybe five tables of people sitting outside.  There was a party happening in the bar area inside, which might explain why it took us such a long time to get our drinks and food, but that party cleared out within 30 minutes of us being there. It was painstaking to order drinks and receive our drinks (we constantly had to ask) and get more water. And once we were finally able to order food close to an hour in, the food probably didn't come for another 40 minutes. Then we couldn't receive our check.  Perhaps the most annoying part of it all was our waiter, who seemed rather flippant about it all and kept laughing heartily as he said sorry about how busy they were (they were not, by the way). He also charged us for two things that never came out and that he said we wouldn't be charged for.  I'm OK with giving this location such a low score because you can head just a few blocks east to the much smaller, much better Green St. location, which is full of nice people who appreciate efficiency. I can't fathom going back to the Chestnut ST. and giving them a third chance.
